apiproto: drop the redundant _XOPEN_SOURCE define

apiproto.h #defines _XOPEN_SOURCE to 700 *after* <stdint.h> has already pulled
in glibc's <features.h>, so it never selects a standard for the includes that
follow (features.h is guarded against re-processing). It only does harm: in a
translation unit that already requested _GNU_SOURCE (e.g. aducsdk.c) features.h
sets _XOPEN_SOURCE to 800, making the line a redefinition-with-different-value
that GCC 15 reports and the project's -Werror turns fatal.

Dropping the line leaves glibc in its default (_DEFAULT_SOURCE) mode, which
already declares the select()/fd_set/usleep() that apiproto.c relies on -
selecting _XOPEN_SOURCE=700 strictly would instead hide usleep() (dropped in
POSIX.1-2008).

Upstream-Status: Pending

--- a/src/utils/apiproto_utils/inc/aduc/apiproto.h
+++ b/src/utils/apiproto_utils/inc/aduc/apiproto.h
@@ -11,7 +11,6 @@
 
 #include "aduc/c_utils.h"
 #include <stdint.h>
-#define _XOPEN_SOURCE 700
 #include <sys/types.h>
 #include <unistd.h>
 
